VAR. Wahbi Khazri stood up, taking
the responsibility, but his effort was denied by Mali goalkeeper Ibrahim
Mounkoro, pulling a wonderful save to protect their lead. Tunisia came into the
tournament in Cameroon following one of the most dominant qualifying runs in
history, where they topped Group A with a healthy seven-points over runners-up
Equatorial Guinea after claiming five wins from six games. They also scored the
second-most goals with 14. Led by the experienced
manager Mondher Kbaier, Tunisia were looking to quickly move on from the Arab
Cup disappointment where they lost in the final, 2-0 to reigning African
champions Algeria last month.